  "issue_title": "[BUG] gitt --version reports 3.2.0 while package version is 5.0.0",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\n`gitt --version` returns `3.2.0`, but the project/package version is `5.0.0` in both `pyproject.toml` and `gittensor/__init__.py`.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Install/run the CLI from the current `test` branch code.\n2. Run:\n   ```bash\n   gitt --version\n   ```\n3. Compare the output with:\n   - `pyproject.toml` (`version = \"5.0.0\"`)\n   - `gittensor/__init__.py` (`__version__ = '5.0.0'`)\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\n`gitt --version` should display `gittensor, version 5.0.0` (or whatever the current package version is).\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\n`gitt --version` displays `gittensor, version 3.2.0`.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Linux\n- Python version: 3.12.3\n- Commit/Version: `test` branch code with package version `5.0.0`\n\n## Additional Context\n\nThe CLI version is currently hardcoded in `gittensor/cli/main.py`:\n- `@click.version_option(version='3.2.0', prog_name='gittensor')`\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-20T21:43:13.000Z",
